<title>UK: Lord Hollick quits Brit.Aerospace as non-exec.</title>
<headline>Lord Hollick quits Brit.Aerospace as non-exec.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Aerospace Plc said Lord Hollick resigned on Wednesday as a non-executive director of the company following his appointment as a special adviser to the Labour government's trade and industry minister Margaret Beckett.  </p>
<p>Bob Bauman, chairman of the company, said in a statement Hollick has played a &quot;key role in helping to shape the transformation of British Aerospace into the competitive, successful company it is today.&quot;</p>
